{"parse":{"title":"thank you","pageid":6449,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|thankyou|thank-you}}\n==English==\n{{phrasebook|en}}\n{{was wotd|2016|November|24}}\n[[File:Thank You (13824254433).jpg|thumb|A “thank you” sign being held up at a [[conference]] in [[Taiwan]] in 2014]]\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|thanke yow}}; as with {{m|en|thank God}}, {{m|en|praise be to God}}, and {{m|en|praise the Lord}}, it was originally a [[present subjunctive]] form but is usually not parsed that way in current usage. It has also sometimes been parsed as a [[prodrop]] form of ([[present indicative]]) ''I thank you'', a mechanism that may plausibly coexist with the other one (instances being variable).\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{a|en|non-æ-tensing}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈθæŋk ˌju/|[ˈθæŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n*** {{audio|en|En-uk-thank you.ogg|a=RP}}\n*** {{audio|en|en-au-thank you.ogg|a=AU}}\n**** {{a|en|th-fronting}}\n***** {{IPA|en|/ˈfæŋk ˌju/|[ˈfæŋk ˌjʊu̯]|a=UK}}\n** {{IPA|en|/ˈðæŋk ˌju/|[ˈðæŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n* {{a|en|æ-tensing}}\n** {{a|en|US|CA}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈθeɪ̯ŋk ˌju/|[ˈθeɪ̯ŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n**** {{audio|en|En-us-thank you 1.ogg|a=non-<<th-stopping>>}}\n**** {{audio|en|En-us-thank you 2.ogg|a=th-stopping}}\n*** {{IPA|en|/ˈðeɪ̯ŋk ˌju/|[ˈðeɪ̯ŋk ˌjʊu̯]}}\n* {{hyph|en|thank|you}}\n\n===Interjection===\n{{en-intj}}\n\n# {{non-gloss|An expression of [[gratitude]] or [[politeness]] in response to something done or given.}} {{defdate|from c. 1400}}\n#: {{ux|en|“'''Thank you'''!” said the girl after her mom gave her a gift.}}\n#: {{ux|en|“And '''thank ''you''''' for being so sweet,” replied her mom.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=attributed to [[w:John Fletcher (playwright)|John Fletcher]]|chapter=[[w:Bonduca|Bonduca, a Tragedy]]|title=The Works of Mr. {{w|Francis Beaumont}}, and Mr. John Fletcher|location=London|publisher=Printed for {{w|Jacob Tonson}}, at Shakespear's Head over-against Catherine-street in the [[w:Strand, London|Strand]]|year=1711|volume=IV|section=act I, scene ii|page=2194|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=3xFEAQAAMAAJ&pg=RA4-PA96|oclc=642500453|passage=''Jun''[''ius''] {{...}} The General has new Wine, new come over. / He muſt have new Acquaintance for it too, / For I will ''none, I '''thank ye'''.'' / ''Pet''[''ilus''] ''None, I '''thank ye'''?'' / A short and touchy answer. ''None, I '''thank ye''''': / Ye do not scorn it, do ye?}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=“G.”|title=The Dukedom (from ‘The News of Literature and Fashion, Science and Art.’)|journal=The Spirit of the Times; or, Essence of the Periodicals; Concentrating Every Week, All that is Worthy (as Strictly Regarding the Time) of Being Preserved, from the Whole of Our Newspapers, Magazines, &c.|location=London|publisher=Printed by Milne, Banfield, and Duckworth [...] for J. Scott|date=22 April 1826|volume=I|issue=XXIX|page=436, column 1|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=JhAbAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA436|oclc=68226152|passage=I had some faint recollection of having a penny-piece in my waistcoat pocket, and, pleased with the service he had rendered to us, I gave it him as his guerdon. \"'''Thank ye''', sir—'''thank ye''', sir—'''thank ye''', sir,\" he cried, and immediately returned to his station near the footway.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=w:Virginia Woolf|title=[[w:Mrs Dalloway|Mrs. Dalloway]]|location=London|publisher=[[w:Leonard Woolf|Leonard]] & {{w|Virginia Woolf}} at the {{w|Hogarth Press}}|date=14 May 1925|oclc=1816789|passage=\"But, '''thank you''', Lucy, oh, '''thank you''',\" said Mrs. Dalloway, and '''thank you''', '''thank you''', she went on saying (sitting down on the sofa with her dress over her knees, her scissors, her silks), '''thank you''', '''thank you''', she went on saying in gratitude to her servants generally for helping her to be like this, to be what she wanted, gentle, generous-hearted.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|author=w:Benny Andersson; w:Björn Ulvaeus|title=w:Thank You for the Music|album={{w|ABBA: The Album}}|artist=w:ABBA|date=12 December 1977|passage='''Thank you''' for the music, the songs I'm singing / Thanks for all the joy they're bringing / Who can live without it, I ask in all honesty / What would life be? / Without a song or a dance what are we? / So I say '''thank you''' for the music / For giving it to me}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Bill Boyd|chapter=Striking a Deal|title=Stepdaddy: A Creative Memoir|location=Macon, Ga.|publisher=w:Mercer University Press|year=2002|page=96|isbn=978-0-86554-781-0|passage='''Thank ya''', ma'am, '''thank ya''', '''thank ya''', '''thank ya'''. He's a good dog. He likes ever'body. He won' be no bother. '''Thank ya''', ma'am, '''thank ya''', '''thank ya'''.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Jerry Goodwin|chapter=Thank You|title=Thank You: One of Seventeen Rules&nbsp;…: Wonderful for Men and Women of All Ages|location=[Philadelphia, Pa.]|publisher=w:Xlibris|year=2007|page=19|isbn=978-1-4257-4126-6|passage=Always say \"'''thank you'''.\" When in doubt, say \"'''thank you'''.\" Say \"'''thank you'''\" even if you think it is not necessary in the circumstances. Whether the recipient thinks it is or is not, it will be appreciated and remembered. It is impossible to say \"'''thank you'''\" too often!}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Colin McEvoy; Lynn Olanoff|chapter=13|title=Fatal Jealousy: The True Story of a Doomed Romance, a Singular Obsession, and a Quadruple Murder|series=St. Martin's True Crime Library|location=New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:St. Martin's Press|St. Martin's Paperbacks]]|month=February|year=2014|page=136|isbn=978-1-250-00971-5|passage=His return text came about an hour later. \"I Love you&nbsp;… For all the right reasons,\" he wrote. \"And I'm glad 2 know u feel the true love u have 4 me again&nbsp;… '''Thank u'''!! You make me feel like i really am superman!!\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=[[w:Roy Williams (playwright)|Roy Williams]]|title=Kingston 14|location=London; New York, N.Y.|publisher=[[w:Bloomsbury Publishing|Bloomsbury Methuen Drama]]|year=2014|section=act II|page=71|isbn=978-1-4725-8826-5|passage=''Adrian'' Shush. / ''Carl'' '''Thank yu'''. / ''Adrian'' Fer what? / ''Carl'' Fer staying. / ''Adrian'' Man tell mi to. Nuh thank mi. But you must shush.}}\n# {{senseid|en|acceptance of an offer}} {{lb|en|often|with ''[[yes]]''}} {{non-gloss|Used as a polite affirmative to accept an offer.}}\n#: {{nearsyn|en|please<id:acceptance of an offer>}}\n#: {{ux|en|—May I help you? —Yes, '''thank you'''.}}\n#: {{ux|en|—May I help you? —'''Thank you'''.}}\n# {{ng|A polite [[dismissal]]; usually used in [[professional]] contexts.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Amy Andrews|title=Limbo|location=Sydney, N.S.W.|publisher=Escape Publishing|year=2015|isbn=978-0-85799-250-5|passage=‘No, come in,’ he said. ‘Martin, right? Have a seat.’ {{...}} ‘'''Thank you''', no, I won’t.’ He moved inside a little more.}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nCan also be used in response to an offer not accepted, as if standing for [[no thank you]]. For example, someone offered a bowl full of strawberries after having already eaten a hearty meal might respond with ''I'm full, '''thank you'''.''\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{l|en|thank u}} {{qualifier|[[eye dialect]], chiefly Internet slang}}\n* {{l|en|thank ya}} {{qualifier|slang}}\n* {{l|en|thank ye}} {{qualifier|archaic}}\n* {{l|en|sank you}} {{qualifier|non-native}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|en|cheers}} {{qualifier|informal}}\n* {{l|en|much appreciated}}\n* {{l|en|gracias}}\n* {{l|en|gramercy}} {{qualifier|archaic}}\n* {{l|en|much obliged}}\n* {{l|en|ta}} {{qualifier|Australia|Britain|New Zealand}}\n* {{l|en|thank you very much}}\n* {{l|en|thanks}}, {{l|en|thanks a bunch}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{l|en|thanks a lot}}, {{l|en|thanks a million}} {{qualifier|informal}}, {{l|en|thanks very much}}\n* {{l|en|ty}} {{qualifier|Internet|text messaging}}\n* ''See also'' [[Thesaurus:thank you]]\n* ''See also'' [[you're welcome]], a typical reply\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|I'm fine, thank you|no thank you|thank-you|thank you card|thank you for coming to my TED Talk|thank-you-ma'am|thank you very much|wham, bam, thank you ma'am| thank you for your attention to this matter}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|yue|thank you|tr=feng{{sup|1}} kiu{{sup|4}}|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|サンキュー|tr=sankyū|サンキュ|tr2=sankyu|センキュー|tr3=senkyū|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ko|땡큐|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ml|താങ്ക്യൂ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|cmn|三Q|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|tl|tenkyu|bor=1}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|an expression of gratitude}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|иҭабуп}}\n* Acehnese: {{tt|ace|teurimong geunaseh}}, {{t|ace|تريموڠ ڬاسيه}}\n* Adangme: {{tt|ada|mo tsumi}}\n* Afar: {{tt|aa|gadda ge}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|dankie}}, {{tt+|af|baie dankie}}, {{t|af|tramma kassie}}\n* Ainu: {{tt|ain|イヤイラィケレ|tr=iyairaykere}} {{qualifier|commonly used}}, {{tt|ain|ハアㇷ゚|tr=haap}}, {{tt|ain|ヒオーィオィ|tr=hioyoy}}\n* Akan: {{tt|ak|me da wo ase}}\n* Aklanon: {{t|akl|saeamat}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|faleminderit}}\n*: Gheg Albanian: {{tt|aln|tu rrit nera}}\n* Aleut: {{tt|ale|qaĝaasakuq}} {{qualifier|Atkan}}, {{tt|ale|qaĝaalakux̂}} {{qualifier|Eastern}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{tt|alt|быйан болзын}}\n* Alutiiq: {{tt|ems|quyanaa}}\n* Ambonese Malay: {{tt|abs|dangke}}\n* American Sign Language: {{tt|ase|OpenB@Chin-PalmBack OpenB@FromChin-PalmUp}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ኣመሰገናልሎ|tr=ʾamäsägnaləlo}}, {{tt|am|አመሰግናለሁ}}\n* Antillean Creole: {{t|gcf|mèsi}}\n* Apache:\n*: Chiricahua: {{tt|apm|ixehe}}\n*: Jicarilla: {{tt|apj|ihéedń}}\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|ahíyi'é}} {{qualifier|San Carlos, Bylas}}, {{tt|apw|áho}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|شُكْرًا}}\n*: Hijazi Arabic: {{tt|acw|شُكْرًا|tr=šukran}}, {{tt|acw|تِسْلَم|tr=tislam}}, {{tt|acw|يِعْطيك العافية|tr=yiʕṭīk al-ʕāfya}}\n*: Juba Arabic: {{t|pga|shukran}}\n*: Moroccan Arabic: {{tt|ary|شكرا|tr=šukran}}, {{tt|ary|بارك الله فيك|tr=bārak ellāh fīk}}, {{tt|ary|الله يبارك فيك|tr=ellāh ybārik fīk}}\n* Aramaic: {{tt|arc|ܬܘܕܝ|tr=tawdi}}\n*: Assyrian Neo-Aramaic: {{tt|aii|ܬܲܘܕܝܼ|tr=tawdī}}, {{tt|aii|ܗܵܘܹܝܬ ܒܲܣܝܼܡܵܐ|tr=hāwēt basīmā}} {{qualifier|to a man}}, {{tt|aii|ܗܵܘܝܵܬܝ ܒܲܣܝܼܡܬܵܐ|tr=hāwyāt basīmtā}} {{qualifier|to a woman}}, {{tt|aii|ܗܵܘܝܼܬܘܿܢ ܒܲܣܝܼܡܹ̈ܐ|tr=hāwīton basīmē}} {{qualifier|to more than one person}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|շնորհակալություն}}, {{tt|hy|շնորհակալ եմ}}, {{t+|hy|մերսի}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|efharisto}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|ধনাবাদ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|gracies}}\n* Avar: {{tt|av|баркала}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|təşəkkür}}, {{tt|az|sağ ol}}, {{tt|az|təşəkkür edirəm}}, {{tt|az|çox razıyam}}\n*: Cyrillic: {{tt|az|тəшəккүр}}, {{tt|az|сағ ол}}, {{tt|az|тəшəккүр едирəм}}, {{tt|az|чох разыjам}}\n*: South Azerbaijani: {{tt|az|تشکر ادرم|tr=tesekkur edirem}}\n* Balinese: {{tt|ban|suksma}}, {{t|ban|matur suksma}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|рәхмәт}}\n* Basque: {{tt+|eu|eskerrik asko}}, {{tt+|eu|mila esker}}, {{tt|eu|esker aunitz}}\n* Batak:\n*: Karo Batak: {{t|btx|ᯆᯬᯐᯮᯒ᯳ᯔᯧᯞᯞ}}, {{t|btx|bujur melala}}\n*: Toba Batak: {{t|bbc|ᯔᯥᯞᯪᯀᯖᯩ}}, {{t|bbc|mauliate}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|дзя́куй}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|ধন্যবাদ}}, {{tt+|bn|শুকরিয়া}}, {{tt+|bn|জাজাকাল্লাহু খাইরান}} {{qualifier|Muslim}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{tt|bho|धन्यवाद}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{tt|bcl|Dyos mabalos}}, {{t+|bcl|salamat}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|trugarez}}\n* British Sign Language: {{t-check|bfi|File:Bsl-thank-you.svg}} <!-- that is one weird entry. badly breaks the layout of the table. is there not a standardised method of textually writing down gestures, like the one we use for ASL? tell [[User talk:Kephir]] -->\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|благодаря́}}, {{tt+|bg|мерси́}}\n* Burmese: {{tt|my|ကျေးဇူးတင်ပါတယ်}}, {{tt|my|[[ကျေးဇူး]][[ပဲ]]}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{tt|rue|дя́кую}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|gràcies}}, {{tt+|ca|moltes gràcies}}, {{tt+|ca|mercès}}\n* Cayuga: {{tt|cay|nya꞉węh}}, {{tt|cay|nya꞉wę}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|salamat}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|osolopaki}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|баркал}}, {{tt|ce|дела реза хуьйла}}, {{tt|ce|саха хуьйла}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎠᎾᎵᎮᎵᎬ}}, {{tt+|chr|